The following subjects are handled in this course: What is physics? Classification of the parts of physics according to: physical processes, objects or research methods. Why should we learn physics? How to make physics interesting - different teaching methods and practical work. Example lessons of different physics topics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to allow students to understand the content of physics study and role on the basic school level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected to: 1. Know the role of physics and the curriculum content of the courses taught in basic school. 2. Know the physics teaching methods and to be able to use them in planning the physics study. 3. Understand the importance of students' motivation and know the ways of supporting it. 4. Know which extracurricular activities can be used to support students' development in physics study.
